The paper deals with lower bounds on the border rank of matrix multiplication, which is a fundamental problem in computational complexity theory. The use of representation theory and obstruction designs suggests a connection to algebraic geometry and geometric complexity theory, which are covered by cs.AG and cs.CG. The paper also involves combinatorial concepts and insights into Kronecker coefficients, which are relevant to cs.DS and cs.SY. Finally, the problem of matrix multiplication is closely related to the study of algorithms and data structures, which fall under cs.CC and cs.SC.
